  "runtime_verified": false,
  "design_reference": "docs/design/12-base-math-shared.md (Chart embedded-object editor shared surface)",
  "chapter": "docs/design/12-base-math-shared.md",
  "note": "Pins the chart embedded-object editor's in-place composition (the OLE-edit toolbar and menubar command identity+order, the sidebar factory routes, and the sidebar panel .ui ids) and grounds the Material treatment in the already-implemented native toolbar Entire/Button parts in definition.xml -- claiming NO new Material chart source. Composition is source-declared only; the custom-drawn drawinglayer chart canvas, live preview, data-table grid, and 3D scene have no .ui and no themeable definition.xml part, so they are build-bound and carved out spec-only below. Registry-closure assignment (chart2/ -> WIN-CH-001) is already satisfied by the prefix rule in bin/check-windows-ui-registry-closure.py, so no registry-closure work is done here. runtime_verified is false throughout: no native build, chart pixels, OLE activation, or runtime interaction are claimed.",
